		<td><b>Re: New Member Introduction</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah there are some parts not fully documented in English yet (like the FDS) but in general the NES is very well reverse engineered and documented for a homebrew community.<br /><br />Regarding PC-Engine, the official English development manual can be found on the internet. It should clear up those contradicting sources, including the confusion of SAT and SATB terminology. According to official documents SAT is basically the PC Engine's OAM (although it is in VRAM) and SATB is a second internal &quot;OAM&quot; of the VDC that must be DMA:d to from SAT (VRAM-SATB DMA) to actually display the sprites. But every homebrew document out there got the terms SAT and SATB backwards (including the debugger in Mednafen).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


